<Review ID>0068929
<Product Name>Creative MuVo TX FM 512 MB MP3 Player Blue
<Title>WOW!!! My first mp3 player
<Date>Sat Sep 10 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>No more cd players for me; feel like I was in the dark ages compared to having this player. This is my first mp3 player and, after much searching for features I wanted, I settled for this. And, I'm not disappointed at all!! The only other feature that I wanted was an expandable memory card slot for additional memory, and I sacrificed that for everything else I got in this player. I have about 80 songs on mine with less than half the memory used up. The battery I had that came with it lasted 3 days; which is good for nonrechargable batteries. I'd advise anyone to get the AAA rechargables if you listen to your mp3 a lot. The software that comes with it is cool, and I learned how to transfer my songs from mp3 to wma format to save more space. The volume is good, the earbuds look of quality and hold up well and fit in my ears nicely. The color is cool, the options are nice when playing a song. I tried out the FM recording and it was alright. Voice recording with anything (just a voice recorder, cellphone, cd player, mp3 player) is good as long as proximity is not a problem. My only headache, trivial as it seems, is the songs don't play in order that they were imported...they play in random order; not a big deal. Plus, the price is great and Creative is a very well known and reliable brand. Buy this and you will not be disappointed!!!!  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>8299319
<Product Name>Creative MuVo TX FM 512 MB MP3 Player Blue
<Title>Buy This MP3 PLayer. Now!!!
<Date>Wed Sep 21 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>I had to pay Creative back in some way for making such a great mp3 player--so I decided to write this review. I bought the player for running and I'm very happy I did. I liked the fact that it came with an armband and cost a lot less than the Ipod that all those suckers at the gym are sporting. The thing is--you don't even need the armband. The player fits into a clip case that you can attach to your waistband--run the cord under you shirt and you don't even feel the thing even when you're running hard. I save my mp3s at a higher quality (I think 192 compared to 128) so I fit about 5 albums on--but you could probably do twice that in WMA. I like to change the content often and it's a sinch. As others have reviewed, the player will alphabetically arrange tracks in a given folder but if your tracks aren't numbered already (and you care) just number them in the title and they'll all play in order. It's also great for experimenting with mixes. This was my first mp3 player and I want to get another one. Buy it!  
<Overall>5

